snippet.textDisplay:
My early connection to Bangla from childhood is a lovely lady who was our nanny in Quetta, Pakistan. I was very young in the 80s and remember her silhouette, few glimpses and some of her sweet Bangla words.
Working in the UK, I have come across a good few lovely people from West Bengal and also Bangladesh, including one very talented singer.
One of my colleagues, originally from Dhaka, speaks excellent Urdu. It puts me to shame not understanding such a sweet melodious and poetic language. 
Lovely to be here and to listen to Bangla under Coke Studio banner.
💚❤
A Pakistani Brit
